{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019n1xfpYKv99SSJ7L6zFNo4","type":"tool_result","content":"title:\tImplement tasks-api Go REST service\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\txlight05\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t1\n--\n## Component Constraints\n- **Name:** tasks-api\n- **Type:** service\n- **Language/Stack:** Go\n- **App Path:** `/tasks-api`\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Expose RESTful API endpoints for task CRUD operations on port 9090\n- Persist tasks in SQLite database with schema: id, description, completed, created_at\n- Validate task descriptions are non-empty before creation\n- Generate unique UUIDs for task identifiers\n- Implement CORS to allow frontend requests from any origin\n- Handle concurrent requests safely with proper database locking\n- Return appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON responses\n- Provide health check endpoint for service monitoring\n- Initialize database schema on startup\n- Implement graceful shutdown for database connections\n\n## Key Considerations\n- Use prepared statements to prevent SQL injection attacks\n- Implement proper error handling and logging to stdout\n- Ensure API is stateless - no session management\n- Handle database connection failures gracefully\n- Support concurrent users without data conflicts through proper locking\n- Validate all input data before processing\n- Use context for request cancellation and timeout handling\n- Return user-friendly error messages with appropriate status codes\n- Trim whitespace from task descriptions during validation\n- Implement optimistic locking or transactions for update operations\n\n## Project Structure Requirements\nCreate a production-ready project structure in the current directory:\n- go.mod with proper module path\n- cmd/ or main.go entry point\n- Dockerfile (multi-stage build)\n- Internal packages as needed (handlers/, services/, models/)\n\nCreate a `workload.yaml` at the root of your component directory:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: openchoreo.dev/v1alpha1\nmetadata:\n  name: <component-k8s-name>\nspec:\n  autoBuild: true\n  autoDeploy: true\n  endpoints:\n    - name: http\n      port: <port-your-app-listens-on>\n      type: HTTP\n      basePath: /\n      visibility:\n        - external\n```\n\nThe port must match the port your application listens on. Adjust endpoint type, basePath, and add dependencies as needed.\n\nThe platform will handle git commit, push, build, and deploy automatically.\n## OpenAPI Spec\n\n```yaml\nopenapi: 3.0.3\ninfo:\n  title: Tasks API\n  version: 1.0.0\n  description: RESTful API for managing todo tasks\npaths:\n  /health:\n    get:\n      summary: Health check endpoint\n      operationId: healthCheck\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Service is healthy\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                type: object\n                properties:\n                  status:\n                    type: string\n                    example: ok\n  /tasks:\n    get:\n      summary: List all tasks\n      operationId: listTasks\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Successfully retrieved tasks\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                type: array\n                items:\n                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/Task'\n        '500':\n          description: Internal server error\n    post:\n      summary: Create a new task\n      operationId: createTask\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n        content:\n          application/json:\n            schema:\n              type: object\n              required:\n                - description\n              properties:\n                description:\n                  type: string\n                  minLength: 1\n                  maxLength: 500\n      responses:\n        '201':\n          description: Task created successfully\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Task'\n        '400':\n          description: Invalid request - description missing or empty\n        '500':\n          description: Internal server error\n  /tasks/{id}:\n    patch:\n      summary: Update task completion status\n      operationId: updateTask\n      parameters:\n        - name: id\n          in: path\n          required: true\n          schema:\n            type: string\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n        content:\n          application/json:\n            schema:\n              type: object\n              required:\n                - completed\n              properties:\n                completed:\n                  type: boolean\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Task updated successfully\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Task'\n        '400':\n          description: Invalid request\n        '404':\n          description: Task not found\n        '500':\n          description: Internal server error\n    delete:\n      summary: Delete a task\n      operationId: deleteTask\n      parameters:\n        - name: id\n          in: path\n          required: true\n          schema:\n            type: string\n      responses:\n        '204':\n          description: Task deleted successfully\n        '404':\n          description: Task not found\n        '500':\n          description: Internal server error\ncomponents:\n  schemas:\n    Task:\n      type: object\n      required:\n        - id\n        - description\n        - completed\n        - createdAt\n      properties:\n        id:\n          type: string\n          description: Unique task identifier\n        description:\n          type: string\n          description: Task description text\n        completed:\n          type: boolean\n          description: Whether the task is completed\n        createdAt:\n          type: string\n          format: date-time\n          description: Task creation timestamp\n```\n\n## Agent Instructions\nBuild a Go REST API service that runs on port 9090 and implements the Tasks API OpenAPI specification. Use net/http for the HTTP server and an in-memory SQLite database (github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3) for persistence. Create a 'tasks' table with columns: id (TEXT PRIMARY KEY), description (TEXT NOT NULL), completed (INTEGER default 0), created_at (DATETIME). Implement endpoints: GET /health (returns {\"status\":\"ok\"}), GET /tasks (list all tasks), POST /tasks (create task with description validation), PATCH /tasks/{id} (update completed status), DELETE /tasks/{id} (remove task). Generate UUIDs for task IDs using github.com/google/uuid. Add CORS middleware allowing all origins with GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE methods. Validate that descriptions are non-empty strings and trim whitespace, returning 400 for invalid input. Use prepared statements to prevent SQL injection. Initialize database schema on startup and handle connection errors gracefully. Return proper HTTP status codes (200, 201, 204, 400, 404, 500) with JSON responses. Log errors to stdout. Implement graceful shutdown to close database connections. Ensure thread-safe concurrent request handling with proper database locking. Use context for request cancellation. The service must be stateless with no session management.\n\n## Working Directory\nYou are working inside a cloned git repository at your component's source directory.\nCreate all files relative to this directory. Do NOT create files outside it.\n\n## General Constraints\n- Write ALL files in the current working directory (do NOT create files outside it).\n- The component must have a Dockerfile for containerized builds.\n- Implement the full API contract from the task — every endpoint must be functional.\n- Use the dependencies listed to understand what other services this component talks to.\n- The app MUST start without any required environment variables — use sensible hardcoded defaults for all config (JWT secrets, DB paths, API URLs, etc.). Environment variables may override defaults but must never be required.\n- Do NOT stub or mock — write real, working implementations.\n- Do NOT run, start, or execute the application server locally. Only write source files. The platform builds and deploys your code automatically — local execution is unnecessary and will cause port conflicts.\n- If you must run a quick compile check (e.g. `go build`, `tsc --noEmit`), do so without starting a server. Never use `go run`, `npm start`, `node server.js`, or any command that starts a long-running process.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa00b97d-e4ab-4b9c-9fa9-810026342600","uuid":"f94ac279-edcb-4296-9148-8363ff4da08a","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:05:08.184Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"title:\tImplement tasks-api Go REST service\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\txlight05\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t1\n--\n## Component Constraints\n- **Name:** tasks-api\n- **Type:** service\n- **Language/Stack:** Go\n- **App Path:** `/tasks-api`\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Expose RESTful API endpoints for task CRUD operations on port 9090\n- Persist tasks in SQLite database with schema: id, description, completed, created_at\n- Validate task descriptions are non-empty before creation\n- Generate unique UUIDs for task identifiers\n- Implement CORS to allow frontend requests from any origin\n- Handle concurrent requests safely with proper database locking\n- Return appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON responses\n- Provide health check endpoint for service monitoring\n- Initialize database schema on startup\n- Implement graceful shutdown for database connections\n\n## Key Considerations\n- Use prepared statements to prevent SQL injection attacks\n- Implement proper error handling and logging to stdout\n- Ensure API is stateless - no session management